node.text:
You know Barbie, but have you met… Barbie? 💖 That’s right; Barbie Roberts meets Barbie Roberts, and they have more in common than just their name! The two became fast friends and chose nicknames inspired by their hometowns – Malibu and Brooklyn – to better differentiate when they’re together.
 
Gather your kids and join the two friends in this dorm room unboxing to get to know #Barbie “Brooklyn” Roberts!

The stories we tell have the power to create a more inclusive world. 📓 In celebration of Hispanic Heritage Month, Barbie is proud to gift Julia Alvarez a one-of-a-kind doll in her likeness, and to honor her legacy in helping to pave the way for more girls to share their stories.
Julia Alvarez is an award-winning Dominican-American writer, educator, and activist, whose vast body of work explores multicultural themes as they relate to children and adults alike. For decades, she has worked to promote literacy as a tool to overcome generational poverty, and remained an outspoken advocate for peace between the Dominican Republic and Haiti.

node.text: In celebration of #HispanicHeritageMonth, Barbie is proud to announce two new one-of-a-kind Role Models in Celia Cruz, the Cuban “Queen of Salsa,” and Dominican-American author and activist Julia Alvarez. node.text: There’s nothing more powerful than using your voice! 🎙️💃 This Hispanic Heritage Month, Barbie is thrilled to honor the memory of the inimitable “Queen of Salsa,” Celia Cruz, with a one-of-a-kind doll in her likeness. As a stage performer, on-screen actor, and recording artist who succeeded in a male-dominated music scene, Celia Cruz is also known as the “Latin Triple Threat.” Her long and storied career serves as endless inspiration for aspiring musicians, and through the Celia Cruz Foundation, her legacy continues to provide scholarships for young Latino students.

node.text: Every fall, many families with roots in Mexico honor their loved ones by celebrating Día de Muertos and commemorating those they’ve lost. Now in its third year of the series, the 2021 Día De Muertos Barbie doll continues to pay tribute to the holiday in a traditional embroidered dress, a crown of marigolds, and symbolic calavera face painting, making this the perfect collectible gift for all who celebrate.
